The '''A1200''' is a touch-screen Motorola Linux phone for [http://www.pokerenfrancais.eu/everest-poker-reveiw/ everest poker].  It was rebranded as "Ming" phone. First available in China and Hong Kong, now available in most markets.  The A1200 comes in 4 flavors, the A1200, A1200i (international version), A1200r (refresh - fixed volume problem with original A1200), and A1200e (supports GSM EDGE).

